Here's what was created:

**`SortableList.razor`** — Generic markup with `@typeparam TItem`. Renders a `<ul>` with each item's `ItemTemplate` plus "Move Up"/"Move Down" buttons. Buttons are disabled at the list boundaries. Uses `@key` for efficient diffing.

**`SortableList.razor.cs`** — Code-behind `partial class` with:
- **`Items`** (`IReadOnlyList<TItem>`) — the input list, copied to a private `_items` field in `OnParametersSet` (never mutated).
- **`ItemTemplate`** (`RenderFragment<TItem>`) — slot for custom rendering via `@context`.
- **`OnOrderChanged`** (`EventCallback<IReadOnlyList<TItem>>`) — fires after each swap, passing a read-only snapshot of the reordered list.

Usage matches your example — the parent updates its own list in `HandleReorder`:

```razor
<SortableList Items="@tasks" OnOrderChanged="HandleReorder">
    <ItemTemplate>
        <span>@context.Title</span>
    </ItemTemplate>
</SortableList>

@code {
    private List<TaskModel> tasks = new() { /* ... */ };
    private void HandleReorder(IReadOnlyList<TaskModel> updated)
    {
        tasks = updated.ToList();
    }
}
```
